BBK01.WT5005: Exchange rates on the Frankfurt exchange /GBP 1 = DM ... / United Kingdom

General: Spot middle rates in Deutsche Mark; difference between buying or selling rate and middle rate in D-Mark: 0.010 up to the end of August 1978 / 0.0070 since September 1978. From 18 May 1953 to 30 December 1998 official quotation on the Frankfurt exchange. In accordance with a resolution by the management board of the Frankfurt exchange, with effect from January 1994 the exchange rate of the Pound sterling was set at four decimal places. For technical reasons, the exchange rates up to December 1993 were extended from three to four decimal places. Please notice: from June 1954 to January 1955 some of the exchange rates for the Pound sterling were quoted with four decimal places. From January 1999, euro reference exchange rates of the European Central Bank; see wt5627. Our specific comments refer to "Frankfurt exchange closed on ..." (Devisenbrse am ... geschlossen) or "Quotation suspended on ..." (Notierung am ... ausgesetzt).
